"title": "2414: cross, centrality of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2414: cross, centrality of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The death of Jesus Christ on the cross is central to the Christian faith. Through the cross and resurrection of Christ, God achieved the redemption of believers and brought hope to the world.</p>\n<h2>The gospel as the ``message of the cross''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:2\">1CO 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17-1Cor1:18\">1CO 1:17–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:23\">1CO 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:1\">GAL 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>The cross redeems from the curse of the law</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:14\">ROM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:4\">ROM 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:19-Gal2:21\">GAL 2:19–2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13-Eph2:16\">EPH 2:13–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:14\">COL 2:13–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a></p>\n<h2>The cross brings reconciliation and justification</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:25\">ROM 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:10\">ROM 5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8-Rom5:9\">ROM 5:8–5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:4\">1CO 15:3–15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:16\">EPH 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:20-Col1:22\">COL 1:20–1:22</a></p>\n<h2>The cross destroys the power of Satan</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:15\">COL 2:13–2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31\">JHN 12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:30\">JHN 14:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:4\">GAL 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14-Heb2:15\">HEB 2:14–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21-1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:21–3:22</a></p>\n<h2>The cross as a stumbling-block or offence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:22-1Cor1:24\">1CO 1:22–1:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:11\">GAL 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:12\">GAL 6:12</a></p>\n<h2>The cross unites believers with Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:4-Rom6:7\">ROM 6:4–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:2\">ROM 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:36\">ROM 8:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:30-1Cor15:31\">1CO 15:30–15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:10-2Cor4:12\">2CO 4:10–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:14-2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:14–5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:16\">EPH 2:14–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:20\">COL 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1-Col3:3\">COL 3:1–3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:11\">2TI 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>The cross as a symbol of discipleship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23-Luke9:24\">LUK 9:23–9:24</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:5–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:38\">MAT 10:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:27\">LUK 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:23-John12:25\">JHN 12:23–12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:26\">EPH 5:25–5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21\">1PE 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></p>",
